definition.value: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 12 in the blood circulation.
The concentration in the blood circulation of a member of the CC chemokine family is outside of normal limits.

label.value: Decreased CSF asialotransferrin to transferrin ratio

definition.value: Increase in diameter of the ejeculatory duct. The ejaculatory duct delivers sperm into the urethra, adding secretions from the prostate and is formed by the union of the vas deferens with the duct of the seminal vesicle.

label.value: Decreased Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome protein concentration in hematopoietic cells

definition.value: The concentration of Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome protein in hematopoietic cells is below the lower limit of normal. This feature is measured by flow cytometry or Western blotting.
Concentration of a complement component in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
The concentration of tetradecenoylcarnitine (C14:1) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
The amount of 2-trans,4-cis-decadienoylcarnitine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Concentration of a catecholamine in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Elevated brain guanidinoacetate level by MRS
Elevated circulating beta chorionic gonadotropin concentration

definition.value: The concentration of interleukin 12 (IL-12) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Reduced circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration

definition.value: The concentration of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Abnormal circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration

definition.value: The concentration of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is outside of the limits of normal.
